children.subject: I'm not an expert on policies, but my understanding is that Math 55 and 70 are comparable and so you should be fine.

history.content:
they don't enforce prerequisites when you enroll, and for a class like 170 i doubt they would enforce them at any point at all

--------------------------------------------

Math + CS accepts Math 55 in lieu of CS 70. The prerequisites of CS 170 are not enforced.

—————————————————

On the enrollment notes it clearly states that prerequisites will be enforced in Week 1.  That sounds to me like if the waitlist was really high, especially with CS majors, they would start kicking out folks without the prerequisites.  I think there’s precedent with the 189 class in the past with the same technique.

—————————————————

^It's certainly a new message, but in the past the class accommodates everyone so I don't imagine they would be kicking people out. 189 is also a class with way higher demand typically and fewer resources (fewer qualified TAs whereas 170 has a really large staff). And 55 is so similar to 70 I can't see them ever booting you from the class for this reason even if it over capacity by week 1. It not unheard of for CS classes to be overfull but it's also not unheard of for CS classes to try various scare tactics to make sure people aren't just willy nilly enrolling in the courses without meeting pre-reqs. I would say OP and the apparently many others who are concerned about 170 enrollment for some reason are fine.
